sentences: William Thomas "Keter" Betts  (July 22, 1928 – August 6, 2005) was an American jazz double bassist.
Early in Betts's career he joined Earl Bostic's R&B band from April 1949- August 1951.
Worked with Bobby Timmons and recorded an album in 1964; began accompanying Ella Fitzgerald in October of that year.
A widowed father of five children, Betts resided in the Washington, DC, area for more than a half century.
He died of a heart attack at his home in Silver Spring, Maryland, in August 2005.
